herman A. Jackson. Unlike other Western and Muslim critiques of violent extremism, this important work emerges from within the movement of Middle Eastern Islamic activism, both challenging and enriching prevailing notions about the role of Islamists in fighting the scourge of extremist politics, blind anti-Westernism and, alas, wayward jihad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJihad. 0aPeacexReligious aspectsxIslam. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aJackson, Sherman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherman, A. Jackson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030019677140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021106140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300211061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300211061/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY